WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.000
Created by ©Yozuki  |  #VisitUs  t.me/Yozukilk

2
00:00:15.290 --> 00:00:17.160
Hey, hey, are you really getting married?!

3
00:00:15.320 --> 00:00:17.160
That's nuts!

4
00:00:15.770 --> 00:00:17.160
<i>Sis...</i>

5
00:00:17.160 --> 00:00:19.170
Knock it off.

6
00:00:17.410 --> 00:00:19.170
Are you going to bring your fiancée to Aso?!

7
00:00:18.250 --> 00:00:19.170
By the way, are there any tasty pastry shops in Tokyo?

8
00:00:19.930 --> 00:00:23.250
<i>I don't answer her calls, 
so now it's a barrage of texts.</i>

9
00:00:23.250 --> 00:00:25.770
<i>She has no idea what I'm dealing with.</i>

10
00:00:25.770 --> 00:00:27.840
<i>But how could she?</i>

11
00:00:28.210 --> 00:00:29.900
<i>It's Thursday already.</i>

12
00:00:29.900 --> 00:00:32.730
<i>I really do have to go back 
to Aso this weekend.</i>

13
00:00:33.170 --> 00:00:37.680
<i>I'll go home, see everyone, and tell them 
the marriage thing is a total lie.</i>

14
00:00:37.680 --> 00:00:39.980
<i>Otherwise, things will get messy.</i>

15
00:00:41.760 --> 00:00:43.540
<i>But what a bother.</i>

16
00:00:43.540 --> 00:00:46.740
<i>Isn't there some way I can do this 
without going home?</i>

17
00:00:48.820 --> 00:00:51.100
<i>The frog stone Honjoji-san gave me.</i>

18
00:00:52.910 --> 00:00:58.540
You're like a lovely couple 
right out of a story.

19
00:00:58.540 --> 00:00:59.860
<i>No, no, no!</i>

20
00:00:59.860 --> 00:01:01.530
<i>I'm sorry, Princess.</i>

21
00:01:01.530 --> 00:01:04.240
<i>That's not... That's not what we're like!</i>

22
00:01:05.030 --> 00:01:08.590
<i>And how do I still feel so good 
when all she did was give me a stone?!</i>

23
00:01:09.010 --> 00:01:11.980
<i>This thing amounts to nothing.</i>

24
00:01:11.980 --> 00:01:17.140
<i>But I wonder why Honjoji-san 
bothered to come all the way here.</i>

25
00:01:17.550 --> 00:01:21.320
So, please stop letting other women 
into your apartment.

26
00:01:22.140 --> 00:01:23.220
<i>Maybe...</i>

27
00:01:23.650 --> 00:01:28.480
Maybe she came to warn me because I'm not 
sticking properly to the fake marriage plan?!

28
00:01:28.810 --> 00:01:30.750
<i>What am I saying, I don't want to go home?</i>

29
00:01:30.750 --> 00:01:32.220
<i>I need to do everything I can!</i>

30
00:01:32.220 --> 00:01:34.760
<i>This plan belongs to us both!</i>

31
00:03:11.960 --> 00:03:14.720
JTC Tourist
 JTC Travel

32
00:03:14.720 --> 00:03:17.220
348 days until

33
00:03:17.220 --> 00:03:20.430
Can We Share Our Lives?

34
00:03:28.350 --> 00:03:31.210
<i>I've been afraid to do anything 
since that day.</i>

35
00:03:31.210 --> 00:03:34.070
<i>It's like, whatever I do, 
I'll make the situation worse.</i>

36
00:03:37.170 --> 00:03:38.900
<i>There go those memories again.</i>

37
00:03:38.900 --> 00:03:41.530
<i>Why did I say such a thing?</i>

38
00:03:41.530 --> 00:03:43.590
<i>It's Friday already.</i>

39
00:03:42.130 --> 00:03:44.400
Well, the data has spoken.

40
00:03:43.590 --> 00:03:45.880
<i>I wonder if Ohara-kun's going home to Aso.</i>

41
00:03:44.400 --> 00:03:48.040
The aquarium is a better 
dating spot than the zoo.

42
00:03:46.100 --> 00:03:48.040
<i>I'd like to ask, but...</i>

43
00:03:48.400 --> 00:03:52.030
<i>Maybe I've been stressed for so long 
it's making me crazy.</i>

44
00:03:52.030 --> 00:03:57.240
<i>I've never been this close to someone, 
and all my thoughts are nonsense.</i>

45
00:03:57.240 --> 00:03:58.980
Oh, that reminds me!

46
00:03:58.980 --> 00:04:02.260
Ohara-san, aren't you going back 
to your folks' place this weekend?

47
00:04:02.820 --> 00:04:04.340
Back home?

48
00:04:04.340 --> 00:04:05.290
The two of you?

49
00:04:05.290 --> 00:04:08.220
Is it that whole "meeting the parents" thing?

50
00:04:08.220 --> 00:04:11.690
<i>Huh? H-How does Gonda-kun know about this?</i>

51
00:04:11.690 --> 00:04:14.690
<i>I haven't told anyone, so who did?!</i>

52
00:04:14.690 --> 00:04:23.780
Isojima

53
00:04:14.950 --> 00:04:17.450
Meeting the parents never goes well, does it?

54
00:04:17.450 --> 00:04:20.340
It sure didn't for me.

55
00:04:20.340 --> 00:04:23.780
After all, my belly was huge 
when I met mine the first time.

56
00:04:23.780 --> 00:04:25.610
<i>W-Wait a minute.</i>

57
00:04:25.610 --> 00:04:27.220
<i>I have to respond somehow.</i>

58
00:04:27.220 --> 00:04:30.250
<i>But I don't know Ohara-kun's plans.</i>

59
00:04:30.250 --> 00:04:31.540
<i>Besides, I...</i>

60
00:04:31.540 --> 00:04:32.790
<i>The way I've been...</i>

61
00:04:33.430 --> 00:04:35.470
<i>If I speak up </i>now<i>,</i>

62
00:04:34.920 --> 00:04:37.300
Please let me know whether the aforementioned hotel is available
 for booking. I will send you more information about the plan.

63
00:04:34.920 --> 00:04:37.300
Wishing you the besssssssssss

64
00:04:35.470 --> 00:04:38.160
<i>who knows what terrible things I'd say?!</i>

65
00:04:38.920 --> 00:04:40.300
It's nothing!

66
00:04:40.570 --> 00:04:43.550
I'm just going back to deal with boring stuff.

67
00:04:43.550 --> 00:04:46.460
Now, go on. Back to work.

68
00:04:46.460 --> 00:04:49.010
Aw, darn.

69
00:04:49.010 --> 00:04:51.320
I was going to ask him all sorts 
of questions once he got back.

70
00:04:49.010 --> 00:04:52.370
Honjoji-san, I'm going to 
make the trip alone.

71
00:04:51.320 --> 00:04:52.370
Yeah, really.

72
00:04:52.770 --> 00:04:56.570
Don't worry, I'll be sure to stick to the plan.

73
00:05:01.280 --> 00:05:03.280
Incoming call
 Number withheld

74
00:05:08.150 --> 00:05:09.120
Yes?

75
00:05:09.120 --> 00:05:11.380
<i>I hear he's going to visit his family.</i>

76
00:05:12.160 --> 00:05:16.520
<i>Of course, you're going to go 
with him, aren't you, Honjoji-san?</i>

77
00:05:16.880 --> 00:05:18.880
Uh, to whom am I speaking?

78
00:05:18.880 --> 00:05:22.740
<i>You're getting married, so 
it's only natural you'd go together.</i>

79
00:05:23.700 --> 00:05:25.850
<i>I'm watching you.</i>

80
00:05:31.640 --> 00:05:33.770
Senmori Animal Clinic

81
00:05:32.520 --> 00:05:36.400
Kama-chan, how've you been?

82
00:05:36.740 --> 00:05:38.590
Settle down!

83
00:05:38.590 --> 00:05:40.020
You don't have an exam today.

84
00:05:40.020 --> 00:05:43.780
You're staying at the Senmori Clinic Hotel!

85
00:05:43.780 --> 00:05:46.820
Thanks. Please look after him.

86
00:05:46.820 --> 00:05:48.050
I'll come get him tomorrow.

87
00:05:48.050 --> 00:05:49.240
Sure thing.

88
00:05:49.240 --> 00:05:51.500
Good thing the hotel wasn't booked up.

89
00:05:51.500 --> 00:05:53.510
I bet Kama-chan's happy too.

90
00:05:53.510 --> 00:05:56.460
This is the number-one cat inn in Kanto.

91
00:05:56.950 --> 00:06:00.750
But you don't usually travel. 
Where are you going?

92
00:06:00.750 --> 00:06:02.970
W-Well, to see my family.

93
00:06:02.970 --> 00:06:06.680
<i>This time it was Honjoji-san 
who received that call.</i>

94
00:06:06.680 --> 00:06:09.600
<i>Who is it? Someone at work?</i>

95
00:06:10.140 --> 00:06:15.120
<i>I'm supposed to do this alone, but now 
we both have to go, thanks to the call.</i>

96
00:06:15.940 --> 00:06:17.630
<i>But I can't see what they're after.</i>

97
00:06:17.630 --> 00:06:19.660
<i>Is it a threat or an obstruction?</i>

98
00:06:19.660 --> 00:06:21.020
<i>Or maybe...</i>

99
00:06:21.020 --> 00:06:24.460
<i>No, one problem at a time.</i>

100
00:06:24.460 --> 00:06:26.320
<i>What to do once we get to my parents'...</i>

101
00:06:26.820 --> 00:06:30.210
<i>I'll go home, and tell them 
the marriage is fake.</i>

102
00:06:30.210 --> 00:06:34.210
<i>Then we'll get them to help 
by not telling work about our plan.</i>

103
00:06:34.690 --> 00:06:37.130
<i>This way we can safeguard the plan,</i>

104
00:06:37.130 --> 00:06:41.210
<i>and it'll just look like she went 
with me to meet my family.</i>

105
00:06:41.210 --> 00:06:43.740
<i>It'd seem unnatural 
to come back the same day.</i>

106
00:06:43.740 --> 00:06:47.240
<i>We'll stay a night at a business hotel 
in Kumamoto, then return to Tokyo.</i>

107
00:06:47.720 --> 00:06:49.010
<i>That'll do it.</i>

108
00:06:47.720 --> 00:06:49.720
Total due

109
00:06:47.720 --> 00:06:49.720
Your bill

110
00:06:47.720 --> 00:06:49.720
Credit

111
00:06:47.720 --> 00:06:49.720
Cash

112
00:06:47.720 --> 00:06:49.720
Your change

113
00:06:47.720 --> 00:06:49.720
Pay

114
00:06:49.720 --> 00:06:51.670
Will you be paying by card?

115
00:06:51.670 --> 00:06:56.070
<i>I've got to pay for Honjoji-san's 
hotel charge and plane ticket.</i>

116
00:06:56.070 --> 00:06:58.630
<i>And I need to thank them 
for covering our shifts at work.</i>

117
00:06:58.630 --> 00:07:00.790
So much money...

118
00:07:00.790 --> 00:07:02.190
It's too expensive?!

119
00:07:02.190 --> 00:07:04.330
Oh, no! I didn't mean that!

120
00:07:04.710 --> 00:07:07.810
Ohara-san, you seem tired.

121
00:07:07.810 --> 00:07:09.950
M-Maybe I am.

122
00:07:09.950 --> 00:07:12.560
I've been dealing with a lot lately.

123
00:07:12.560 --> 00:07:13.980
Is that so?

124
00:07:13.980 --> 00:07:17.390
I'm afraid I don't have any 
medicine for humans here.

125
00:07:17.390 --> 00:07:19.350
All I can do is cheer for you.

126
00:07:19.750 --> 00:07:21.650
Go! Go! Ohara-san!

127
00:07:21.650 --> 00:07:23.660
You can do it, Ohara-san!

128
00:07:23.660 --> 00:07:24.760
Huh?

129
00:07:24.760 --> 00:07:29.760
Senmori Animal Clinic

130
00:07:25.870 --> 00:07:28.900
<i>She's a good doctor, but an oddball.</i>

131
00:07:29.770 --> 00:07:33.560
<i>Kama, I don't want to 
leave you behind either.</i>

132
00:07:33.560 --> 00:07:36.390
<i>This is so we can keep living together.</i>

133
00:07:36.390 --> 00:07:40.140
<i>This plan belongs to me, 
Honjoji-san, and you.</i>

134
00:07:40.140 --> 00:07:42.280
<i>All three of us!</i>

135
00:07:43.150 --> 00:07:46.150
Mount Aso

136
00:07:46.750 --> 00:07:50.140
<i>I'm a little relieved 
now that we're both going.</i>

137
00:07:50.510 --> 00:07:53.570
<i>Because the truth is, I owe them an apology.</i>

138
00:07:53.920 --> 00:07:58.850
<i>But I have yet to figure out 
how to apologize.</i>

139
00:08:00.790 --> 00:08:02.480
<i>I had better get ready.</i>

140
00:08:04.260 --> 00:08:06.800
<i>What should I wear?</i>

141
00:08:06.800 --> 00:08:08.690
<i>I have no idea.</i>

142
00:08:09.260 --> 00:08:11.760
Hey, is this okay?

143
00:08:11.760 --> 00:08:13.720
High-Quality Maps

144
00:08:11.760 --> 00:08:13.720
Is it okay?

145
00:08:13.720 --> 00:08:17.550
Hey, are these clothes okay to wear there?

146
00:08:17.550 --> 00:08:19.730
Are they, Mommy?

147
00:08:19.730 --> 00:08:22.860
You can decide what clothes 
to wear, can't you?

148
00:08:23.280 --> 00:08:26.870
But when I decide, it looks bad.

149
00:08:26.870 --> 00:08:28.640
That's not true.

150
00:08:28.640 --> 00:08:31.240
Just wear what you'd like to wear.

151
00:08:32.090 --> 00:08:35.590
Rika-san, you should be more confident.

152
00:08:36.010 --> 00:08:38.660
You're a very smart girl.

153
00:08:50.460 --> 00:08:52.220
It's about that time.

154
00:09:06.530 --> 00:09:08.530
Sorry to keep you waiting.

155
00:09:11.870 --> 00:09:13.530
N-No problem!

156
00:09:13.530 --> 00:09:17.080
<i>W-Wow, Honjoji-san in travel mode.</i>

157
00:09:17.080 --> 00:09:19.550
<i>Why did I show up wearing a </i>backpack<i>?</i>

158
00:09:18.540 --> 00:09:20.200
Okinawa

159
00:09:18.540 --> 00:09:21.040
Sapporo

160
00:09:18.540 --> 00:09:21.040
Kumamoto

161
00:09:18.540 --> 00:09:21.040
Hachijo-jima

162
00:09:18.540 --> 00:09:21.040
Nakashibetsu

163
00:09:18.700 --> 00:09:21.040
Okayama

164
00:09:28.300 --> 00:09:30.050
<i>Don't get the wrong idea.</i>

165
00:09:30.050 --> 00:09:32.610
<i>This is a trip to tell them it's a lie.</i>

166
00:09:33.680 --> 00:09:38.210
<i>But it sure does feel like she's 
going to meet her future in-laws.</i>

167
00:09:42.020 --> 00:09:43.670
<i>Kumamoto, huh?</i>

168
00:09:43.670 --> 00:09:46.270
<i>Was this a good outfit to choose?</i>

169
00:09:46.270 --> 00:09:52.040
<i>But I have no idea what's a good outfit 
for revealing a lie to a coworker's family.</i>

170
00:09:52.660 --> 00:09:56.990
Um, have you ever been to Kumamoto?

171
00:09:56.990 --> 00:09:58.940
I have.

172
00:09:59.430 --> 00:10:01.220
Several times, when I was a child.

173
00:10:01.220 --> 00:10:03.380
Were those family vacations?

174
00:10:05.930 --> 00:10:07.630
Something like that.

175
00:10:07.630 --> 00:10:10.270
<i>Why'd she react like that?</i>

176
00:10:10.270 --> 00:10:12.280
<i>Did I ask a weird question?</i>

177
00:10:12.280 --> 00:10:14.640
<i>It's not like me to 
make conversation like this.</i>

178
00:10:15.790 --> 00:10:17.600
Uh, Ohara-kun!

179
00:10:17.960 --> 00:10:20.760
Do you want to hear about my family?

180
00:10:22.530 --> 00:10:28.360
I've heard all about you, but 
I haven't talked about myself at all.

181
00:10:28.990 --> 00:10:31.630
Y-You don't need to feel obligated.

182
00:10:31.630 --> 00:10:36.070
Not at all! But it might come up 
in conversation at some point.

183
00:10:37.860 --> 00:10:40.240
Then I would like to hear.

184
00:10:40.900 --> 00:10:44.290
O-Okay, I will talk about my family.

185
00:10:44.840 --> 00:10:47.540
Although, I'm not sure what to say.

186
00:10:47.910 --> 00:10:50.380
It's not an especially engaging topic.

187
00:10:50.750 --> 00:10:54.630
What was your childhood like?

188
00:10:54.950 --> 00:10:56.770
My childhood?

189
00:10:57.920 --> 00:11:00.370
Not much different from now.

190
00:11:06.560 --> 00:11:08.520
High-Quality Maps

191
00:11:12.890 --> 00:11:14.420
I'm home!

192
00:11:16.650 --> 00:11:18.990
My father wasn't around,

193
00:11:18.990 --> 00:11:21.430
so my mother and I lived by ourselves.

194
00:11:21.830 --> 00:11:25.330
Rika-san,
 I have to go to Fukuyama in Hiroshima
 for work. Sorry this happens so much.
 Ms. Aki will come check on you at night. 
If anything comes up, be sure to call me.
 The hotel I'm staying at is the
 Fukuyama Mountain Inn.

195
00:11:22.100 --> 00:11:26.280
My mother had to go on business 
trips all over the place,

196
00:11:26.280 --> 00:11:29.740
so I was often the only one at home.

197
00:11:29.740 --> 00:11:31.340
Fukuyama.

198
00:11:43.680 --> 00:11:45.810
Kobe

199
