Higashiosaka

203
00:11:43.680 --> 00:11:45.810
Nara

204
00:11:43.680 --> 00:11:45.810
Kashihara

205
00:11:43.680 --> 00:11:45.810
Nara

206
00:11:43.680 --> 00:11:45.810
Osaka Bay

207
00:11:43.680 --> 00:11:45.810
Wakayama

208
00:11:43.680 --> 00:11:45.810
Kii Mountains

209
00:11:48.610 --> 00:11:53.070
I spent most of my time alone 
looking at maps.

210
00:11:53.430 --> 00:11:55.730
You really <i>haven't</i> changed much.

211
00:11:56.900 --> 00:11:59.410
Rika-san, I have to go to Fukuyama in Hiroshima for work. Sorry this happens so much.

212
00:11:57.890 --> 00:12:01.080
Fukuyama, Fukuyama.

213
00:12:01.080 --> 00:12:03.810
Fukuyama in Hiroshima.

214
00:12:03.810 --> 00:12:04.890
Found it!

215
00:12:04.890 --> 00:12:07.030
It's the fifth time for Hiroshima.

216
00:12:07.410 --> 00:12:12.390
That's far away. How would you 
get there from Tachikawa?

217
00:12:15.950 --> 00:12:16.870
Mommy.

218
00:12:17.520 --> 00:12:18.760
Me.

219
00:12:19.080 --> 00:12:22.630
Mommy and I are departing Tachikawa!

220
00:12:22.630 --> 00:12:25.690
Our destination, Fukuyama in Hiroshima!

221
00:12:25.690 --> 00:12:28.980
I passed the time playing like that.

222
00:12:31.700 --> 00:12:32.970
It's Mount Fuji!

223
00:12:32.970 --> 00:12:34.730
You can see it now!

224
00:12:35.070 --> 00:12:36.740
It sure is tall.

225
00:12:37.040 --> 00:12:39.740
Wow, Mommy! Look how tall it is!

226
00:12:42.680 --> 00:12:44.710
Honjoji residence.

227
00:12:44.710 --> 00:12:46.590
Oh, Ms. Aki.

228
00:12:46.590 --> 00:12:50.510
<i>Sorry, Rika-chan. I'll be over 
as soon as I'm off work.</i>

229
00:12:50.510 --> 00:12:53.330
It's okay, I ate some strawberries.

230
00:12:53.330 --> 00:12:55.750
<i>I really am sorry!</i>

231
00:12:56.130 --> 00:12:59.850
<i>I bet you're lonely, 
always at home by yourself.</i>

232
00:12:59.850 --> 00:13:03.660
<i>Shame on your mommy! 
She should spend more time at home.</i>

233
00:13:04.120 --> 00:13:06.520
I'm not lonely at all.

234
00:13:06.520 --> 00:13:08.920
Mom's working hard for her job.

235
00:13:08.920 --> 00:13:11.020
And I'm good at minding the house.

236
00:13:12.360 --> 00:13:14.170
Now, how far did we get?

237
00:13:14.170 --> 00:13:16.420
Oh, right! We're at Fukuyama already!

238
00:13:16.790 --> 00:13:20.400
Yay, we've arrived! It's Fukuyama!

239
00:13:20.400 --> 00:13:21.650
It has a harbor!

