247
00:13:21.650 --> 00:13:25.780
It has mountains, and islands, 
and wow! A castle, too!

248
00:13:25.780 --> 00:13:29.190
I like this city! I wonder what it's like!

249
00:13:31.210 --> 00:13:32.960
Fukuda

250
00:13:31.210 --> 00:13:32.960
Higashiodo

251
00:13:31.210 --> 00:13:32.960
Renjuku & former 
residence of Suga Chazan

252
00:13:31.210 --> 00:13:32.960
Kasaoka

253
00:13:31.210 --> 00:13:32.960
Fukuyama Castle Ruins

254
00:13:31.210 --> 00:13:32.960
Fukuyama

255
00:13:31.210 --> 00:13:32.960
Remains of Kusado Sengen

256
00:13:31.210 --> 00:13:32.960
Minomi

257
00:13:34.960 --> 00:13:36.960
Renjuku & former 
residence of Suga Chazan

258
00:13:34.960 --> 00:13:36.960
Kasaoka

259
00:13:34.960 --> 00:13:36.960
Fukuyama Castle Ruins

260
00:13:34.960 --> 00:13:36.960
Fukuyama

261
00:13:34.960 --> 00:13:36.960
Remains of Kusado Sengen

262
00:13:52.390 --> 00:13:55.200
Wow, you can see the ocean!

263
00:13:55.200 --> 00:13:58.430
It's amazing, Mommy! 
Let's go to the hotel next!

264
00:13:58.430 --> 00:14:00.740
I wonder what route we'll take!

265
00:14:01.740 --> 00:14:04.230
P-Pretty boring topic.

266
00:14:04.230 --> 00:14:05.240
No.

267
00:14:05.540 --> 00:14:08.210
It isn't boring at all.

268
00:14:09.080 --> 00:14:11.630
O-Oh, okay.

269
00:14:15.390 --> 00:14:17.250
<i>Here I am. Home.</i>

270
00:14:17.590 --> 00:14:19.460
Uh, best of luck to us both.

271
00:14:19.460 --> 00:14:21.490
I'll do everything I can, too.

272
00:14:21.490 --> 00:14:23.820
Yes, let's get this done.

273
00:14:23.820 --> 00:14:24.800
Right.

274
00:14:24.800 --> 00:14:26.310
Taku-chan.

275
00:14:28.630 --> 00:14:29.970
Grandma?!

276
00:14:39.980 --> 00:14:41.480
Grandma?!

277
00:14:41.480 --> 00:14:44.740
Bless my soul! You're back in Kumamoto!

278
00:14:44.740 --> 00:14:45.870
Y-Yeah.

279
00:14:45.870 --> 00:14:48.390
Been a long time, ain't it?

280
00:14:48.390 --> 00:14:49.240
"Grandma"?

281
00:14:49.990 --> 00:14:52.830
Um, this is my grandmother. 
On my father's side.

282
00:14:53.800 --> 00:14:55.250
What brings you here?

283
00:14:55.570 --> 00:14:59.220
I was bringin' melons to the airport.

284
00:14:59.220 --> 00:15:03.360
You know Ogata-san? 
He said he'd sell some here for us.

285
00:15:00.750 --> 00:15:04.260
Grown in Kumamoto Prefecture

286
00:15:03.360 --> 00:15:06.800
Oh listen here, you need a lift?

287
00:15:06.800 --> 00:15:07.500
Huh?

288
00:15:07.500 --> 00:15:09.510
Ain't you goin' home to Aso?

289
00:15:09.510 --> 00:15:11.180
W-Well, yes.

290
00:15:13.510 --> 00:15:15.520
Mom, we're here!

291
00:15:15.520 --> 00:15:18.520
Haruko, Izumi. Make yourselves at home.

292
00:15:21.180 --> 00:15:23.360
Huh? Where're you going, Dad?

293
00:15:24.040 --> 00:15:26.910
To your grandma's to help with shipping.

294
00:15:26.910 --> 00:15:29.710
Takuya'll be here by the time I'm done.

295
00:15:30.740 --> 00:15:33.600
Speaking of which, what time 
<i>is</i> Taku-chan getting here?

296
00:15:33.600 --> 00:15:34.370
Beats me.

297
00:15:34.700 --> 00:15:36.650
I tried callin', but he didn't answer.

298
00:15:36.650 --> 00:15:38.880
I also texted, but no response.

299
00:15:40.360 --> 00:15:44.880
If he's gettin' married, he coulda 
let us know sooner than this.

300
00:15:44.880 --> 00:15:48.390
Maybe he don't wanna talk 
to his scary big sisters.

301
00:15:48.390 --> 00:15:50.470
Aww, we ain't scary.

302
00:15:50.470 --> 00:15:53.110
Tokyo's way scarier than us.

303
00:15:54.020 --> 00:15:57.980
How many years since you
been back this way, Taku-chan?

304
00:15:57.980 --> 00:16:00.810
By the way, who's that with you?

305
00:16:02.130 --> 00:16:05.610
U-Um, my name is Honjoji.

306
00:16:05.610 --> 00:16:08.630
I'm Ohara-san's, um, coworker.

307
00:16:08.630 --> 00:16:11.490
Well ain't you the cutest thing!

308
00:16:11.490 --> 00:16:13.270
Knock that off!

309
00:16:13.270 --> 00:16:15.450
Oh yeah, I plumb forgot!

310
00:16:15.450 --> 00:16:17.930
Ain't you gettin' married, Taku-chan?

311
00:16:17.930 --> 00:16:20.360
Don't tell me she's the lucky lady?

312
00:16:21.170 --> 00:16:23.710
Koichi mentioned it a number of times.

313
00:16:23.710 --> 00:16:26.960
Said Taku-chan had himself a wife-to-be 
and was comin' home.

314
00:16:26.960 --> 00:16:28.380
<i>What?!</i>

315
00:16:28.780 --> 00:16:32.550
Um, that whole story is a lie!

316
00:16:35.070 --> 00:16:35.970
What?!

317
00:16:36.250 --> 00:16:39.300
We aren't going to get married.

318
00:16:39.300 --> 00:16:42.960
I'm sorry for any trouble 
it's caused everyone here.

319
00:16:42.960 --> 00:16:46.990
That's right. 
It's not like that at all with us.

320
00:16:51.720 --> 00:16:54.490
Sounds like you got a lot on your plates.

321
00:16:55.700 --> 00:16:58.200
Fruit

322
00:16:58.200 --> 00:17:02.140
We're here. Have some 
melon or somethin' before you go.

323
00:17:02.140 --> 00:17:04.590
But, we need to get to the house.

324
00:17:04.590 --> 00:17:07.090
You can spare a minute.

325
00:17:07.090 --> 00:17:10.580
You used to be thrilled to come by.

326
00:17:10.580 --> 00:17:12.990
We grow fruit here.

327
00:17:12.990 --> 00:17:15.340
Would you like some to take home?

328
00:17:18.390 --> 00:17:20.700
We're gettin' these ready to ship.

329
00:17:20.700 --> 00:17:23.640
Your grandpa's got a strained back now.

330
00:17:23.640 --> 00:17:25.650
I've been workin' on this by my lonesome.

331
00:17:25.650 --> 00:17:27.230
Aww, it hurts!

332
00:17:27.230 --> 00:17:29.080
I'll help you box them.

333
00:17:29.080 --> 00:17:30.430
Oh yeah?

334
00:17:30.430 --> 00:17:33.460
Well then, maybe I'll go snip some melons.

335
00:17:33.820 --> 00:17:35.360
Grown in Kumamoto Prefecture

336
00:17:37.130 --> 00:17:40.200
Sorry, Honjoji-san. This won't take long.

337
00:17:48.090 --> 00:17:49.640
Excuse me, ma'am.

338
00:17:49.640 --> 00:17:52.390
Is there anything I can help with?

339
00:17:52.720 --> 00:17:55.860
You bet. Wanna try snippin' melons?

340
00:17:55.860 --> 00:17:57.060
Ever done it?

341
00:17:57.060 --> 00:17:58.500
No, never.

342
00:17:58.500 --> 00:18:01.740
Aww, anybody can do it.

343
00:18:01.740 --> 00:18:04.730
But not in those clothes.

344
00:18:04.730 --> 00:18:06.890
You go ahead and put this on.

345
00:18:06.890 --> 00:18:07.980
Okay.

346
00:18:10.240 --> 00:18:13.030
Sorry. It's none too stylish.

347
00:18:13.030 --> 00:18:14.450
It's fine.

348
00:18:14.790 --> 00:18:17.700
You snip with the clippers.

349
00:18:17.700 --> 00:18:20.350
But not too close to the fruit.

350
00:18:20.350 --> 00:18:21.350
All right.

351
00:18:23.510 --> 00:18:27.870
<i>I've come to reveal a lie, and 
somehow, I'm harvesting melons.</i>

352
00:18:30.590 --> 00:18:32.300
<i>It's hot.</i>

353
00:18:37.880 --> 00:18:39.890
<i>This is such nice scenery.</i>

354
00:18:40.230 --> 00:18:42.980
<i>Come to think of it, 
this is an ancient caldera.</i>

355
00:18:43.380 --> 00:18:48.070
<i>Where magma once flowed, 
people are living and farming,</i>

356
00:18:48.070 --> 00:18:49.580
<i>and even trains pass through.</i>

357
00:18:50.310 --> 00:18:53.080
<i>Human activity is amazing.</i>

358
00:18:53.940 --> 00:18:55.030
<i>Oh, whoops.</i>

359
00:18:55.030 --> 00:18:57.260
<i>This is no time to be 
captivated by the terrain.</i>

360
00:18:59.170 --> 00:19:00.870
Long time no see, Grandpa.

361
00:19:00.870 --> 00:19:02.620
Aww, it hurts.

362
00:19:02.620 --> 00:19:04.340
Is your back okay?

363
00:19:04.340 --> 00:19:06.080
Aww, it hurts!

364
00:19:08.590 --> 00:19:10.280
Bet you're tuckered out.

365
00:19:10.280 --> 00:19:13.060
Try some melon. Here.

366
00:19:13.060 --> 00:19:13.840
All right.

367
00:19:17.140 --> 00:19:18.440
It's good!

368
00:19:18.440 --> 00:19:19.980
Sure is!

369
00:19:19.980 --> 00:19:23.100
We put a lotta hard work into our melons.

370
00:19:23.370 --> 00:19:25.280
Your fields are magnificent.

371
00:19:25.280 --> 00:19:29.140
Are they? I'm so used to seein' 'em.

372
00:19:29.560 --> 00:19:33.040
Used to be fields all over the place here.

373
00:19:33.040 --> 00:19:36.400
Grapes, melons, strawberries, everywhere.

374
00:19:36.400 --> 00:19:38.830
But it's shrunk down a lot now.

375
00:19:38.830 --> 00:19:43.170
And people used to work so much, 
they nearly never went inside.

376
00:19:43.870 --> 00:19:46.220
Grandpa, you want to watch TV?

377
00:19:46.220 --> 00:19:48.000
Aww, its hurts.

378
00:19:48.000 --> 00:19:50.900
Just so much less now.

379
00:19:50.900 --> 00:19:52.480
I see.

380
00:19:53.200 --> 00:19:55.960
You don't gotta hide it, hon.

381
00:19:57.120 --> 00:19:59.890
You two actually <i>are</i> gettin' married, ain't ya?

382
00:20:00.870 --> 00:20:03.140
I can tell.

383
00:20:04.180 --> 00:20:07.140
Wisdom comes with age.

384
00:20:07.540 --> 00:20:12.140
Ma'am, please listen! 
We really aren't going to get married!

385
00:20:12.140 --> 00:20:15.440
Because Taku-chan said 
he was comin' back to Aso.

386
00:20:15.440 --> 00:20:18.450
It'd be hard for him to announce 
he's gettin' married anywhere else.

387
00:20:18.890 --> 00:20:22.360
The men in our family are bad 
with words, and stubborn to boot,

388
00:20:22.360 --> 00:20:24.430
which is a pain when things get complicated.

389
00:20:24.430 --> 00:20:28.210
This land's important to Koichi, 
but he mustn't be unreasonable.

390
00:20:28.210 --> 00:20:31.200
Taku-chan should just ignore his complaints.

391
00:20:31.200 --> 00:20:34.840
He's so awkward. 
Must make things hard for you.

392
00:20:34.840 --> 00:20:37.710
<i>I'm the same way, so I can't comment.</i>

393
00:20:38.400 --> 00:20:40.470
But listen here, hon.

394
00:20:40.940 --> 00:20:45.220
Try to always get along with Taku-chan.

395
00:20:46.330 --> 00:20:49.980
I reckon y'all got things 
you can't talk about,

396
00:20:50.480 --> 00:20:53.790
but if he's happy, then I'm happy.

397
00:20:53.790 --> 00:20:56.990
It was easy to tell when I saw his face.

398
00:20:57.330 --> 00:21:00.770
He really does care for you.

399
00:21:03.410 --> 00:21:05.240
You take good care of him.

400
00:21:05.240 --> 00:21:08.120
U-Um, ma'am! It's not like that!

401
00:21:08.120 --> 00:21:09.510
It's not like...

402
00:21:11.790 --> 00:21:13.230
Hon?

403
00:21:15.480 --> 00:21:19.000
Oh no, heatstroke! Someone help!

404
00:21:19.000 --> 00:21:21.760
Taku-chan, come quick!

405
00:21:26.880 --> 00:21:28.620
H-Honjoji-san!

406
00:21:28.620 --> 00:21:30.100
I'll ring Dr. Whiskers.

407
00:21:30.100 --> 00:21:31.880
You get her inside.

408
00:21:31.880 --> 00:21:33.150
A-All right.

409
00:21:33.150 --> 00:21:35.680
Carry her gently. Gently!

410
00:21:36.420 --> 00:21:37.900
U-Um...

411
00:21:38.350 --> 00:21:41.050
Um... Um...

412
00:21:42.360 --> 00:21:44.430
You're gonna be okay!

413
00:21:45.870 --> 00:21:47.870
Aww, it hurts!

414
00:21:47.870 --> 00:21:49.630
<i>Sh-She's heavy!</i>

415
00:21:49.630 --> 00:21:51.230
<i>My back's gonna break!</i>

416
00:21:51.850 --> 00:21:54.080
The doctor said he'll make a house call!

417
00:21:54.080 --> 00:21:56.550
Taku-chan, you can go in through here!

418
00:21:56.550 --> 00:21:59.050
A-All right. Open it for me, Grandma!

419
